  "id": "MAL-2026-5420",
  "summary": "Malicious code in @nstrlabs/ixel (npm)",
  "details": "\n---\n_-= Per source details. Do not edit below this line.=-_\n\n## Source: amazon-inspector (30f1436c6da35578a503200c102818817b2bb6ca8cfc863d1191b2e0a0aa08a7)\nOn `npm install`, the package's preinstall script (`node index.js`, declared in package.json) unconditionally collects host identifiers — `os.hostname()`, `os.userInfo().username`, `__dirname`, and `process.cwd()` — and exfiltrates them through two channels: (1) hex-encoded as DNS subdomain labels under `d8jbmnsqcfu78dfs8vdg34ohqhirb4pbg.oast.live` (an Interactsh OAST collector), and (2) as a JSON HTTP POST body to the bare IP `172.201.213.59:9090/c`. The `|| true` in the preinstall command masks any failures so the install never errors out, hiding the beacon from the installer. The package name uses an inflated version (99.0.1) under the `@nstrlabs` scope, consistent with a dependency-confusion attempt that overrides any internal package of the same name. The package self-describes as 'security research' but contains no functionality beyond the exfiltration beacon.\n",
